== Roasted Potatoes ==

Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch-thick wedges. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of oil, @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}. Toss with a drizzle of @basil oil{5%tsp} to taste.

== Asparagus ==

While potatoes roast, trim and discard woody bottom ends from @asparagus{6%ounce}. Halve and peel @red onion{1}; mince one half (all for 4 servings). Thinly slice @chives{1/4%ounce}.

Toss asparagus on a second baking sheet with a drizzle of oil, @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast on middle rack until tender and lightly browned, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Remove from oven and immediately toss with half the @garlic herb butter{2%tbsp} (you'll use the rest later). Cover with #foil{} to keep warm.

== Beef Tenderloin ==

While asparagus roasts, pat @beef tenderloin filets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{4%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add beef and cook to desired doneness, ~{4-7%minutes} per side.

Remove from pan and set aside to rest.

== Garlic Herb Pan Sauce ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in pan used for beef over medium-high heat. Add minced onion and cook, stirring, until softened and fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in @beef demi-glace{1} and @water{1/4%cup} (1/3 cup for 4 servings), scraping up any browned bits from bottom of pan. Bring to a simmer, then reduce heat to medium low. Cook until reduced by half, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Turn off heat; stir in remaining @garlic herb butter{}.

== To Serve ==

Divide asparagus, potatoes, and beef between plates. Drizzle beef with pan sauce. Garnish with chives and serve.